    "headline": "Amazon opens up its logistics network to other businesses",
    "summary": "Amazon.com said on Monday it was rolling out \"Amazon ‌Supply Chain Services\", opening up its ‌logistics network for other businesses to use.  Businesses ​of all types and sizes can now move, store and deliver everything from raw materials to final products using ‌the full breadth ⁠of Amazon's own supply-chain network, including freight, distribution and fulfillment, ⁠and parcel shipping, the company said.  The announcement hit shares of logistics companies, ​with UPS ​and FedEx ​slipping 1.5% and ‌2.5%, respectively, in premarket trading.",
