  {
    "ts": "2026-05-04T10:09:22+00:00",
    "headline": "Amazon opens up its logistics network to other businesses in growth push",
    "summary": "Amazon.com is opening the supply-chain network that has powered its operations for decades to other businesses, pitting it directly ‌against logistics heavyweights such as UPS and FedEx.  \"Amazon Supply Chain Services\" will allow companies ‌across industries such as retail, healthcare and manufacturing to use the tech giant's freight network spanning ocean, road, rail and air ​to move, store and deliver everything from raw materials to final products.  With this, Amazon will unlock a new growth opportunity for its e-commerce unit, building on a service that supports thousands of independent third-party sellers worldwide.",
    "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/amazon-opens-logistics-network-other-100922260.html",
